Source: guadalinex-meta
Section: base
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Carlos Parra Camargo <cparra@emergya.info> 
Standards-Version: 3.7.2
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4), germinate (>= 0.21ubuntu1)

Package: guadalinex-minimal
Architecture: any
Depends: ${guadalinex-minimal:Depends}
Recommends: ${guadalinex-minimal:Recommends}
Description: Minimal core of Guadalinex 
 This package depends on all of the packages in the Ubuntu minimal system,
 that is a functional command-line system with the following capabilities:
 .
  - Boot
  - Detect hardware
  - Connect to a network
  - Install packages
  - Perform basic diagnostics
 .
 It is also used to help ensure proper upgrades, so it is recommended that
 it not be removed.

Package: guadalinex-standard
Architecture: any
Depends: ${guadalinex-standard:Depends}
Recommends: ${guadalinex-standard:Recommends}
Description: The Guadalinex standard system
 This package depends on all of the packages in the Guadalinex standard 
 system. This set of packages provides a comfortable command-line Unix-like
 environment.
 .
 It is also used to help ensure proper upgrades, so it is recommended that
 it not be removed.

Package: guadalinex-desktop
Architecture: any
Depends: ${guadalinex-desktop:Depends}
Recommends: ${guadalinex-desktop:Recommends}
Description: The Guadalinex desktop system
 This package depends on all of the packages in the Guadalinex desktop system
 .
 It is also used to help ensure proper upgrades, so it is recommended that
 it not be removed.
